7215120/http://starbisnov.ro/en/ Star Bisnov], Website for Banat Bulgarian people\n\n{{Ethnic groups in Romania}}\n{{Ethnic groups in Serbia}}\n{{Bulgarian diaspora}}\n\n[[Category:Banat Bulgarian people| ]]\n[[Category:Bulgarian minorities|Banat]]\n[[Category:Bulgarian diaspora]]\n[[Category:Ethnic groups in Bulgaria]]\n[[Category:Ethnic groups in Romania]]\n[[Category:Ethnic groups in Serbia]]\n[[Category:Ethnic groups in Transylvania]]\n[[Category:Ethnic groups in Vojvodina]]\n[[Category:Slavic ethnic groups]]\n[[Category:Sub-ethnic groups]]\n", "name_user": "Wbm1058", "label": "safe", "comment": "Timi\u0219oara(viaWP:JWB)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Banat_Bulgarians"}
{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Nebraska", "text_new": "{{Current disaster|event=pandemic|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Nebraska\n| width           = \n| image           = \n| image_size      = \n| image_upright   = \n| alt             = \n| caption         = \n| map1            = \n| legend1         =\n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| map4            = \n| legend4         = \n| map5            = \n| legend5         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Nebraska]], U.S.\n| first_case      = [[Omaha, Nebraska|Omaha]]\n| arrival_date    = March 6, 2020\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], China via [[California]], U.S.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n| confirmed_cases = 153<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=http://dhhs.ne.gov/Pages/Coronavirus.aspx|title=Coronavirus Disease 2019 (COVID-19) {{!}} Health & Human Services|website=dhhs.ne.gov|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n| suspected_cases = \n| severe_cases    = \n| recovery_cases  = \n| deaths          = 2<ref name=\":0\" />\n| territories     = \n| total_ili       = \n| website         = {{URL|http://dhhs.ne.gov/Pages/Coronavirus.aspx}}\n}}\nThe 2020 coronavirus pandemic in the [[U.S. state]] of [[Nebraska]] is part of an [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|ongoing worldwide pandemic]] of [[coronavirus disease 2019]] ({{nowrap|COVID-19}}), a novel infectious disease caused by [[severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus&nbsp;2]] ({{nowrap|SARS-CoV-2}}). As of March 29, 2020, the Nebraska Department of Heath and Human Services has confirmed 120 cases and 2 deaths in the state.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Timeline==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/United States/Nebraska medical cases chart}}\n\nOn March 13, the Nebraska Department of Health and Human Services (DHHS) set up a coronavirus (COVID-19) information line that will allow residents to get answers to general questions and receive information on resources available.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dhhs.ne.gov/Pages/Statewide-COVID-19-Information-Line-Opens-for-Residents.aspx/|title=Statewide COVID-19 Information Line Opens For Residents|website=DHHS|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref>\n\nOn March 27, the first and second deaths related to coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19) were reported to the Nebraska Department of Health and Human Services (DHHS).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dhhs.ne.gov/Pages/Two-COVID-19-Deaths-Reported-in-State.aspx/|title=Two COVID-19 Deaths Reported In State|website=DHHS|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>\n\n==Statistics==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:right\"\n! colspan=\"3\" |COVID-19 Cases in Nebraska<ref name=\":0\" />\nUpdated March 29, 2020\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" |County\n! scope=\"col\" |Confirmed Cases\n! scope=\"col\" |Deaths\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Adams County, Nebraska|Adams]]\n|3\n|0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Buffalo County, Nebraska|Buffalo]]\n|6\n|0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Cass County, Nebraska|Cass]]\n|2\n|0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Dawson\u00a0County, Nebraska|Dawson]]\n|1\n|0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Dodge\u00a0County, Nebraska|Dodge]]\n|3\n|0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Douglas County, Nebraska|Douglas]]\n|78\n|1\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Gosper County, Nebraska|Gosper]]\n|1\n|0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Hall County, Nebraska|Hall]]\n|6\n|1\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Kearney County, Nebraska|Kearney]]\n|1\n|0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Knox County, Nebraska|Knox]]\n|2\n|0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Lancaster County, Nebraska|Lancaster]]\n|8\n|0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Lincoln County, Nebraska|Lincoln]]\n|5\n|0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Madison County, Nebraska|Madison]]\n|2\n|0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Nemaha County, Nebraska|Nemaha]]\n|1\n|0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Platte County, Nebraska|Platte]]\n|1\n|0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Sarpy County, Nebraska|Sarpy]]\n|14\n|0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Saunders County, Nebraska|Saunders]]\n|2\n|0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Scotts Bluff\u00a0County, Nebraska|Scotts Bluff]]\n|1\n|0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Washington County, Nebraska|Washington]]\n|12\n|0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[York County, Nebraska|York]]\n|1\n|0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |TBD\n|3\n|0\n|- class=\"sortbottom\"\n! style=\"text-align:right;\" |Total\n! style=\"text-align:right;\" |153\n! style=\"text-align:right;\" |2\n|}\n\nNOTE: Both state and local health departments are testing and publicly reporting their cases. In the event of a discrepancy between DHHS cases and cases reported by local public health officials, data reported by the local health department should be considered the most up to date.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Mask reuse experiments==\n\nAmid shortages of personal protective equipment, the [[University of Nebraska Medical Center]] is experimenting with using [[UV light]] to disinfect and reuse masks.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kolata |first1=Gina |title=As Coronavirus Looms, Mask Shortage Gives Rise to Promising Approach |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/20/health/coronavirus-masks-reuse.html |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=The New York Times |date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Directed Health Measures==\n\nGovernor [[Pete Ricketts]] issued two [[Directed Health Measure]]s to restrict gatherings in Cass, Douglas, Sarpy, Lancaster, Dodge, and Saunders counties.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://governor.nebraska.gov/sites/governor.nebraska.gov/files/doc/press/Governor%20Press%20Release%203-19%20-%20SPANISH.pdf|title=Gov. Ricketts Announces Directed Health Measure for Cass, Douglas, Sarpy, & Washington Counties|date=March 19, 2020|website=governor.nebraska.gov}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://governor.nebraska.gov/press/gov-ricketts-adds-lancaster-saunders-and-dodge-directed-health-measure-cass-douglas-sarpy|title=Gov. Ricketts Adds Lancaster, Saunders, and Dodge to Directed Health Measure for Cass, Douglas, Sarpy, & Washington Counties|website=governor.nebraska.gov}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://dhhs.ne.gov/Pages/Coronavirus.aspx/ Information] from the Nebraska Department of Health and Human Services\n* [https://nebraska.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/4213f719a45647bc873ffb58783ffef3 Coronavirus COVID-19 Nebraska Cases Dashboard] from the Nebraska Department of Health and Human Services\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States}}\n{{Portal bar|Medicine|United States|Viruses|Coronavirus disease 2019|Pandemic}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in Nebraska]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States by state|Nebraska]]\n\n\n{{Nebraska-stub}}\n{{COVID-19-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Current disaster|event=pandemic|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Nebraska\n| width           = \n| image           = \n| image_size      = \n| image_upright   = \n| alt             = \n| caption         = \n| map1            = \n| legend1         =\n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| map4            = \n| legend4         = \n| map5            = \n| legend5         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Nebraska]], U.S.\n| first_case      = [[Omaha, Nebraska|Omaha]]\n| arrival_date    = March 6, 2020\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], China via [[California]], U.S.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n| confirmed_cases = 153<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=http://dhhs.ne.gov/Pages/Coronavirus.aspx|title=Coronavirus Disease 2019 (COVID-19) {{!}} Health & Human Services|website=dhhs.ne.gov|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n| suspected_cases = \n| severe_cases    = \n| recovery_cases  = \n| deaths          = 2<ref name=\":0\" />\n| territories     = \n| total_ili       = \n| website         = {{URL|http://dhhs.ne.gov/Pages/Coronavirus.aspx}}\n}}\nThe 2020 coronavirus pandemic in the [[U.S. state]] of [[Nebraska]] is part of an [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|ongoing worldwide pandemic]] of [[coronavirus disease 2019]] ({{nowrap|COVID-19}}), a novel infectious disease caused by [[severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus&nbsp;2]] ({{nowrap|SARS-CoV-2}}). As of March 29, 2020, the Nebraska Department of Heath and Human Services has confirmed 120 cases and 2 deaths in the state.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Timeline==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/United States/Nebraska medical cases chart}}\n\nOn March 13, the Nebraska Department of Health and Human Services (DHHS) set up a coronavirus (COVID-19) information line that will allow residents to get answers to general questions and receive information on resources available.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dhhs.ne.gov/Pages/Statewide-COVID-19-Information-Line-Opens-for-Residents.aspx/|title=Statewide COVID-19 Information Line Opens For Residents|website=DHHS|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref>\n\nOn March 27, the first and second deaths related to coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19) were reported to the Nebraska Department of Health and Human Services (DHHS).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dhhs.ne.gov/Pages/Two-COVID-19-Deaths-Reported-in-State.aspx/|title=Two COVID-19 Deaths Reported In State|website=DHHS|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>\n\n==Statistics==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:right\"\n! colspan=\"3\" |COVID-19 Cases in Nebraska<ref name=\":0\" />\nUpdated March 29, 2020\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" |County\n! scope=\"col\" |Confirmed Cases\n! scope=\"col\" |Deaths\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Adams County, Nebraska|Adams]]\n|3\n|0\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Buffalo County, Nebras